The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Vizag Steel, NTPC in power pact

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Hyderabad, April 9: Rashtriya Ispat Nigam (RINL) will set up a joint venture with NTPC to produce 150 mw power annually in Visakhapatnam.

 RINL chairman and managing director Y. Shiv Sagar Rao said both the companies would pick up 50 per cent equity each in the project estimated to cost Rs 700 crore.

 We will sign the MoU next week and plan to begin commercial production by 2009, he said.

 RINL, the corporate entity of Vizag Steel Plant, also plans to set up an SPV with SAIL, NTPC, NMDC and CIL to explore coking coal reserves and mining in Australia and the US.

 The proposal for the SPV with a corpus of Rs 10,000 to Rs 25,000 crore is pending before the cabinet. 




